      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I agree that there is a gaping hole in our society that should be filled with culture and the arts rather than with the trial du jour and the latest blow-'em-up movie.</p>
        <p>I have to wonder, however, how many questions on standardized tests are devoted to appreciating the works of Faulkner or Hemingway. How can we expect children to establish a love of learning when we take all of the exploratory fun out of it? Not everything can be boiled down to a multiple-choice question.</p>
        <p>Kristin Camplese  State College, Pa., June 16, 2005</p>
        <p>The writer is an educational consultant.</p>
      </block>
